Panagiotis Vasilopoulos (born 1985, Athens) is a Greek professional basketball player.  He was a member of the Greece national basketball team that finished second in the 2006 FIBA World Championship.  He is a small forward but he can also play as a center or power forward. He is curently plays for Olympiacos BC and he has a two-year contract.









